<br>
EDIT: EXP is in part based on damage like you said Terea. I say this because if one group is doing a clear majority of damage (&gt; 60%), they will usually have one person on the top of the aggro list. However, aggro still doles out how EXP is divided. My theory is that whichever group has the MOST people in the top X slots of the aggro list, they will get the EXP (Just a theory though, never really had any reason to try it).<br>
<br>
Despite what you think, there wasn't any bug that I can recall that would cause DD's to do 0 aggro points. If this were true then why would Wizards get aggro for nuking? IF your theory was true we could chain nuke until we were blue and the face and never get turned on. Before the change a while ago to the way the aggro list operates most of the EXP groups in the planes were Wizard/Caster groups. You mainly had to start a very large nuke (Ice Comet, Rend, etc) when the MOB was at about 50%, and when it finished casting the MOB would be near death. The nuke would land and if you were lucky get the kill shot. Before the cahnge I would say more than 70% of kill shots yielded EXP. This was because if you got the last nuke in on something it would bump you to the top of the aggro list. Back then aggro lists were limited to 6 sltos or something MUCH smaller than they are now. One nuke could jump you to the top of the aggro list, thereby giving you EXP. The main thing they changed in that patch was they added more slots to the aggro list. Now the tanks and other melee stay on the aggro list much longer than they did before, making it easier for them to get EXP on raids. It is still possible for use to KS, it just takes a lot of high-taunt spells like stuns and large nukes. </font><P><P align=center>
